==English==
===Noun===
'''space cadet'''

# {{slang}} term for someone who deals with [[reality]] in a way consistent with being under the influence of (or "spaced out on") drugs. The term may also be used in jest for someone who forgets, [[daydream]]s, or otherwise is distracted from reality more often than most. Another meaning popular in British English is taken from the word space meaning "empty" indicating that someone referred to as a space cadet is lacking in the grey matter department or to put it plainly, "has an empty head".